What you need to know:

The historic win, which Morans fought to the last second for victory, means Kenya cannot finish below third place in Group B of the Afrobasket qualifiers which are being held at the Palais Polyvalent des Sports Complex here in Yaounde on Saturday.As was the case on Friday when they lost 69-51 to Senegal in the opening match of the qualifiers, the Morans started the match against Angola sluggishly, and found themselves 22-9 at the end of the first quarter.